cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses resource management in cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel closed-form spectral efficiency derivation, which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of millimeter-wave transmissions in cellular networks, which is a topic related to multimedia communication. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new approach to resource management in cellular networks, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper briefly mentions the power consumption and peak-to-average power ratio (PAPR) of mobile users, which is related to hardware architecture.
